		<item>
			<title>Access to funding: NGO to start registration of NGOs</title>
			<link>http://www.dailytrust.com.ng/index.php/news/175351-access-to-funding-ngo-to-start-registration-of-ngos</link>
			<guid>http://www.dailytrust.com.ng/index.php/news/175351-access-to-funding-ngo-to-start-registration-of-ngos</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.dailytrust.com.ng/images/stories/a poster from the forum.jpg" border="0" /></p>
<p><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><strong><span style="color: #800000;">A poster portraying the plight of poor rural women at the Forum today</span></strong></span><span style="color: #800000;"><br /></span></p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">A Non Governmental Organisation, Partnership for Rural Women Development has said it will embark on registration of Non Governmental Organisations in the country to get a data base of all genuine NGOs to strengthen their credibility for access to funding from donors.</span></strong></p>
<p>“We will come up with a directory of the NGOs that are credible in the society. And  I think we will use that to dialogue with funders, international agencies to look at the way forward,”  the National Coordinator of the Partnership for Rural Women Development , Zainab Muahammed  said  at the ongoing at the stakeholders’ forum for partnership for rural women development.</p>
<p>She said the forum was organised to get the best way to help alleviate poverty among rural women in terms of developing their capacity to fend for themselves.</p>
<p>A participant, Mrs Margaret Ahmad painted gory picture of poverty among rural women by narrating a story of a woman who she said rejoiced after learning how to bake cake by saying “my children will not die again.”</p>
<p>“Even the programmes that are designed for rural women, rural women don’t know anything about it. And yet reports are written, and money is signed,” she said.</p>
<p>She explained that rural women are very accessible as they are always ready to learn how to better their economic fortunes.</p>
<p>{jathumbnail off}</p>]]></description>
			<author>abdulwasiihassan@yahoo.com (Abdulwasiu Hassan)</author>
